as apparent to us then that there had been a sea change in how companies, from mission-driven small businesses to corporate giants, were interacting with societal issues and grappling with fitting their broader responsibilities into their strategy for maximizing profit. The answer is that those responsibilities often *donâ€™t* neatly fit into that strategy; you need a new strategy. </p><p>In the past year we have seen a swell of ideas about this, whether in the Business Roundtableâ€™s updated statement on the purpose of the corporation or in the many thoughtful pieces on the topic that various experts have contributed to Quartz At Work. And then there are the books ... so many excellent, interesting, thought-provoking books that we are starting to see more and more of, about the promise and pitfalls of leading socially responsible businesses. We rounded up a few of our favorites for you as the capstone to the 2019 edition of our Perfect Company project, The New Purpose of Companies. Please enjoy.</p></details></div><div class="_528b6" itemProp="about" itemscope="" itemType="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><a class="_12036" href="/co/2864502/five-books-to-read-now-about-the-purpose-of-companies/"><div class="_58631" itemProp="image" itemscope="" itemType="https://schema.org/imageObject"><div class="_2e8cc a1afd visible" style="padding-bottom:100%"><img src="https://i0.wp.com/qz-news.imgix.net/2864502/thumbnail?auto=compress" srcSet="https://i0.wp.com/qz-news.imgix.net/2864502/thumbnail?auto=compress&amp;w=150&amp;h=150&amp;crop=1&amp;strip=all&amp;quality=75 150w, https://i0.wp.com/qz-news.imgix.net/2864502/thumbnail?auto=compress&amp;w=200&amp;h=200&amp;crop=1&amp;strip=all&amp;quality=75 200w" sizes="(max-width: 26.5624em) 150px, (min-width: 48em) 200px, 200px" alt="" class="" decoding="async"/></div><meta itemProp="url" content="https://i0.wp.com/qz-news.imgix.net/2864502/thumbnail?auto=compress"/></div><div class="_71aea"><h3 itemProp="headline" class="_095bb">Fi